    <string name="voice_input_info_title">Voice Input Setup</string>
    <string name="voice_input_info_message">Gboard uses its own Google speech engine and ignores the system voice input setting.\n\nTo use Polished Recognition:\n\n1. Install AnySoftKeyboard (free on F-Droid / Play Store)\n2. In Our Settings Screen, tap \"Set as Voice Input\" to set Polished Recognition as the system default\n3. Switch to AnySoftKeyboard (globe key next to your spacebar) and press the microphone button\n\nTo set the recognition service manually:\n\n  Settings → Language &amp; input → Voice input → Polished Recognition\n\nIf the setting is hidden (e.g. Samsung Android 11), use ADB:\n\n  adb shell settings put secure voice_recognition_service\n    com.georgernstgraf.polishedrecognition/com.georgernstgraf.polishedrecognition.service.PolishedRecognitionService\n\n  Verify:\n  adb shell settings get secure voice_recognition_service</string>
